This paper deals with the semantics of self-adjusting computation, which is a topic that falls under programming languages (cs.PL) and logic in computer science (cs.LO). The paper also discusses change propagation and memoization, which are concepts related to data structures (cs.DS) and software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper uses a logical framework to formalize the semantics and meta-theory, which is a topic that falls under distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
